Super Eagles star Cyriel Dessers has received his third award of the season as he has been voted Feyenoord’s Player of the month for April. Dessers has had a stellar campaign since he left Genk for Feyenoord last summer. The Super Eagles star has become the lynchpin for the former Eredivisie champions and has also established his legend in the Europa Conference League, helping his side to the finals with ten goals and two assists.   NBBF to get Interim Management Committee     Super Eagles’ Olayinka linked to €2m La Liga move     Teams laud NLO over sanctions to erring clubs   Last month Dessers was fantastic for Feyenoord, scoring four goals and assisting two in seven games. The Super Eagles star was instrumental in Feyenoord’s qualification for the final of the maiden Conference League. The 27-year-old has now been recognized for his performance in the month, as Feyenoord have announced him as their Player of the month for April. Dessers is not a stranger to awards, as he was the player of the month last November. He also won the goal of the month award in November.